parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column and Intermediate Shaft Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column and intermediate shaft can cause the steering wheel to become loose, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal switch can cause other drivers to misinterpret the vehicle's intentions, leading to accidents and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the tie rods can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation or lag in acceleration can cause accidents, especially when merging or passing other vehicles.
